{
  "texts": [
    "The structure of the algorithm mainly consists of two parts: a novel cylindrical image representation of a 3D point cloud and an efficient descriptor based on contexts and layouts of the scenes.",
    "Additionally, a sequence-based temporal consistency check is introduced to handle similar scenes and local structural changes.",
    "OverlapNet (Chen et al. 2021) is a loop closing method for 3D LiDAR-based SLAM.",
    "It exploits the different cues generated from the point cloud such as range, normal, and intensity images, and semantic data to provide overlap and relative yaw angle estimates between pairs of 3D scans.",
    "The 3D point cloud is first converted to a 2D image, and the rotation information is represented as translation of the image."
  ]
}